    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my bathroom sink is dripping constantly a bit thru the handle like a compression faucet thing. what tools do i need to fix it and how do i change the washer?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You need a wrench, a screwdriver, and a bucket of water to fix your dripping faucet, which is a classic plumbing grommet issue. First, you'll need to loosen the handle to access the nut underneath, then use the wrench to unscrew the nut and pull out the old washer. Once you've removed the old washer, you'll need to buy a new one from a hardware store or a plumbing supply, then slide it back in and tighten the nut until it's snug but not overtightened. Finally, you'll need to turn the handle back on to test the fix.\n\nThe grommet is the rubber seal that holds the washer in place, and if it's worn or cracked, water will leak through the handle. You can buy a replacement grommet at any hardware store, or even a bottle cap if you're feeling adventurous. Just make sure to replace the washer too, as the grommet alone won't stop the dripping if the washer is old or damaged. Once you've installed the new grommet and washer, turn the handle back on and check for any leaks before you use the sink. If the problem persists, you might need to check the pipe for cracks or leaks, but",
